    {
      "id": "d2d868f2_4ae5d17f",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/contrib/requirements.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 26,
      "message": "How about using tags instead of conditions?\nhttps://v2.helm.sh/docs/developing_charts/#chart-dependencies\n\nthis should allow us to deploy or not all components used for testing with a single toggle. What do you think?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-08 21:18:21.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a11f2c17_c88d1664",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/contrib/requirements.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 26,
      "message": "That’s exactly what does global.addTestingComponents value. And tags are of « or » model, meaning that we cannot start if two Tags are set. \n\nMoreover, condition can be derived from override (like this one) whereas I’m not sure for tags. So for use case override, I’m not really sure...\n\nLast, condition and tags doesn’t really work with « deploy » plugin which basically Check if « enabled » is true or false 😞\n\nI propose to leave it as is and look how we can be better in Guilin (contrib subcomponents as requirements for some components, redesign deploy, see if we need deploy when using helm3, ...)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2319,
        "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
        "username": "sdesbure"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-08 21:41:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d2d868f2_4ae5d17f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
